## Advanced Usage

### High-Frequency Machines (60fps)

For game loops or high-frequency updates, disable metadata tracking:

```typescript
const gameMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'game',
  trackMetadata: false, // Critical: avoids GC thrashing
  slices: {
    player: createSlice({
      id: 'player',
      initial: { x: 0, y: 0 },
      cache: { policy: 'session' },
      reducers: {
        move: (state, { x, y }: { x: number; y: number }) => {
          state.x = x;
          state.y = y;
        },
      },
    }),
  },
  context: { userID: null },
});
```

### Custom Selectors

Compute derived state efficiently:

```typescript
const shopMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'shop',
  slices: { cart: cartSlice, products: productsSlice },
  selectors: {
    cartTotal: (state) =>
      state.cart.items.reduce((sum, item) => {
        const product = state.products.byId[item.productId];
        return sum + (product?.price ?? 0) * item.quantity;
      }, 0),
    itemCount: (state) =>
      state.cart.items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.quantity, 0),
  },
  context: { userID: null },
});

// Access directly
function CartSummary() {
  const total = shopMachine.useMachine('cartTotal');
  const count = shopMachine.useMachine('itemCount');
  return <div>{count} items: ${total}</div>;
}
```

### Cache Invalidation Handling

Handle stale data after cache invalidation:

```typescript
const machine = createMachine({
  id: 'app',
  slices: { user: userSlice },
  initial: cachedState, // Hydrated from storage
  context: { userID: currentUserId },
});

// Check for invalidations
if (machine.invalidations) {
  const { stale, reset } = machine.invalidations;

  // Slices that need refetching (SWR mode)
  if (stale.length) {
    stale.forEach(sliceKey => {
      machine.actions[sliceKey]?.load?.();
    });
  }

  // Slices that were fully reset
  console.log('Reset slices:', reset);
}
```

### Context Management

Provide runtime dependencies to slices:

```typescript
const appMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'app',
  slices: { data: dataSlice },
  context: {
    userID: null,
    api: apiClient,
    analytics: analyticsService,
  },
});

// Update context after login
function onLogin(user: User) {
  appMachine.provideContext({
    userID: user.id,
  });
}
```

