## TypeScript Support

### Type Inference

All APIs are fully typed with automatic inference:

```typescript
// Schema type inference
const UserSchema = createModel({
  id: 'number',
  name: 'string',
  email: 'string?',
  roles: 'string[]',
});

type User = InferType<typeof UserSchema>;
// { id: number; name: string; email?: string; roles: string[] }

// Machine state inference
type AppState = InferMachineState<typeof appMachine>;
```

### Utility Types

Available type utilities from `@zazcart/toolkit`:

| Type                     | Description                        |
|--------------------------|------------------------------------|
| `Writable<T>`            | Remove readonly modifiers          |
| `Compute<T>`             | Flatten intersection types         |
| `Paths<T>`               | All dot-notation paths of object   |
| `PathType<T, P>`         | Type at specific path              |
| `Falsy`                  | Union of falsy values              |
| `UnionToIntersection<T>` | Convert union to intersection      |
| `NullableToPartial<T>`   | Convert nullable props to optional |
| `Serializable`           | JSON-serializable types            |
| `AnyFunction`            | Generic function type              |
| `PromiseValue<T>`        | Extract resolved type from Promise |

